President Obama announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Milford Wayne Donaldson, President of Architect Milford Wayne Donaldson, FAIA, Inc., will be appointed as Chairman of the Advisory Council on Historic Preservation. Clement Alexander Price, Board of Governors Distinguished Service Professor of History at Rutgers University, will be appointed as Vice Chairman of the Advisory Council on Historic Preservation. Harry P. Hallock, Deputy Assistant Secretary of the Army for Procurement, will be appointed as a member of the Committee for Purchase from People Who Are Blind or Severely Disabled. Tom Robinson, Associate Deputy Assistant Secretary for Headquarters U.S. Air Force, will also be appointed as a member of the Committee for Purchase from People Who Are Blind or Severely Disabled. President Obama expressed his gratitude for their willingness to serve and looks forward to working with them.